	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				By the way, regarding the tower in UR:<BR>
<BR>
Camping the tower is possible with mid-20's fairly <BR>
easily as long as certain conditions are met.  First,<BR>
the bar should be camped also. The two rooms are <BR>
linked as far as the mobs go, so if one is camped<BR>
without the other, that room will get trained <BR>
when the other spawns.  If both bar and tower are<BR>
camped by full groups, all either room has to worry<BR>
about is its own mobs.  Second, the tower group <BR>
needs the right mix.  A good mix I've found is three<BR>
tanks, two clerics and a druid/ranger/shaman or nuker.  A<BR>
group too cleric heavy won't work as well because<BR>
A) the knight and hags resist expluse and even <BR>
dismiss quite a bit and B) you want three melee <BR>
types at least to keep hitting the hags so they <BR>
can't cast.  Having one or two tanks only bashing<BR>
on a hag, especially using a slower 2H like BIBS, <BR>
is inviting trouble.  Having a nuker is nice for <BR>
the bats that show up and are invulnerable to <BR>
expulse/dismiss, but you can get by without one.<BR>
Third, everyone in the group needs to know their <BR>
roles and play them, and trust one another.  Tanks<BR>
keep nasties off the clerics/casters, clerics heal<BR>
and med, everyone keeps everyone buffed, no one panic,<BR>
all that stuff.  If you can meet all these conditions,<BR>
the tower is ironically one of the safest places<BR>
in UR for a group of 24ish types.  Case in point, <BR>
last night I camped it for three or four hours with<BR>
a very good group, got three bubbs, didn't die once<BR>
and got great loot (didn't even come CLOSE to dying). <BR>
On my way back to the zone to head back to GF I<BR>
got trained by the bar near the fountains, had<BR>
two or three drys and a monk on me all at once, and<BR>
made it to Cauldron with like 15 HP left.  My group<BR>
in the tower was howling as they saw my HP drop. <BR>
<BR>
Knight drops mantles at least 4 to 1 over tunics.<BR>
Knight is not all that tough for a group of 24s to <BR>
take down.  Greater dark bones are tougher I think.<BR>
Hags are wimps if you DON'T ALLOW THEM TO CAST.  Can't<BR>
stress that enough.  Oh yeah, the knight will harm<BR>
touch the first PC it hits, usually for 200 HP or<BR>
so depending on your magic resist. <BR>
<BR>
A
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
